            "html": "<strong>1. Step 1: Cut Out Paper for Stand</strong><div class='step-images count-2'><figure><img src='https://content.instructables.com/FU3/4PJI/L3N9HVBV/FU34PJIL3N9HVBV.jpg?auto=webp&fit=bounds&frame=1&height=1024auto=webp&frame=1&height=300&auto=webp&fit=bounds&width=600&height=450&quality=75' alt='Cut Out Paper for Stand' loading='lazy'></figure><figure><img src='https://content.instructables.com/FP8/LMQN/L3N9HVBT/FP8LMQNL3N9HVBT.jpg?auto=webp&fit=bounds&frame=1&width=1024auto=webp&frame=1&height=300&auto=webp&fit=bounds&width=600&height=450&quality=75' alt='Cut Out Paper for Stand' loading='lazy'></figure></div><p><strong>Étapes :</strong></p><ol><li><ul><li>Measure the dimensions of your phone on the paper.</li><li>Mark dimensions which are smaller than the phone and as per requirement of the stand. I have used 3 inch x 2inch rectangle for my smartphone which should work for almost all phones generally. Keep a margin of 1 inch as free space. Let's say the length of the mark is l (small L, (3 inches)) and the breadth of the mark is b (2 inches).</li><li>Now, the length of the cutout from the paper required = L' = 2* (l + b) = 10 inches and the width should be 4 inches (this is fixed).</li><li>This is because the stand is a 3d box-shape. For making the 3x2, we require a rectangle of 3x2 dimensions multiplied by the height of the stand.</li></ul></li></ol>",
